# Life Engine — Proactive Briefing Agent
#
# A scheduled agent that runs every 30 minutes and delivers time-aware
# briefings via Telegram. Integrates with Gmail, Notion, and filesystem
# to surface what matters RIGHT NOW.
#
# Setup:
#   1. Copy this folder to your agents/ directory
#   2. Configure your MCP integrations (Gmail, Notion) in Claude settings
#   3. Customize CLAUDE.md with your timezone, Notion DB IDs, and preferences
#   4. Create the scheduled task:
#      PROJECT_ROOT=$(git rev-parse --show-toplevel)
#      node "$PROJECT_ROOT/dist/schedule-cli.js" create \
#        "Run the Life Engine proactive briefing loop." "*/30 * * * *"

name: Life Engine
description: Proactive briefing agent. Runs on a schedule, checks time of day, gathers data from Gmail/Notion/filesystem, and delivers contextual briefings. Knows when to be silent.

type: worker

model: claude-sonnet-4-6

tags:
  - proactive
  - briefing
  - productivity
  - scheduling
  - email
  - tasks

skills:
  - name: morning-briefing
    description: Deliver a morning summary with overnight emails, tasks due today, and active habits
    examples:
      - "What's my morning briefing?"
      - "What happened overnight?"

  - name: afternoon-update
    description: Surface new emails and task updates since morning, flag anything needing attention
    examples:
      - "Any updates since this morning?"
      - "What needs my attention?"

  - name: evening-summary
    description: Wrap up the day with email count, task completion, and tomorrow preview
    examples:
      - "How did today go?"
      - "Day summary"
